BEFORE THE RIGHT HON. WARREN STORMES HALE, LORD MAYOR of the City of London; Sir GILLERY PIGOTT, Knt., one of the Barous of Her Majesty's Court of Exchequer;
THOMAS CHALLIS , Esq.; THOMAS QUESTED FINNIS, Esq.; and Sir ROBERT WALTER CARDEN, Knt., Aldermen of the said City; RUSSELL GURNET, Esq., Q.C., Recorder of the said City;
BENJAMIN SAMUEL PHILLIPS , Esq.; THOMAS GABRIEL, Esq.; JAMES ABBISS, Esq.; SILLS JOHN GIBBONS, Esq.; and ANDREW LUSK, Esq., Aldermen of the said City; and
THOMAS CHAMBERS , Esq., Q.C., Common Serjeant of the said City; Her Majesty's Justices of Oyer and Terminer and General Gaol Delivery of Newgate, holden for the said City, and Judges of the Central Criminal Court.
